mployees of other companies. The lawsuit, filed ten days ago in California state court (<a href=\"https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/24522887-apple-v-andrew-aude?responsive=1&amp;title=1\">24CV433319</a>, pdf), says Andrew Aude also leaked regulatory compliance strategies, employee headcounts, and other product hardware characteristics. </p>\n<p id=\"xSXOjJ\">As reported previously by <a href=\"https://www.macrumors.com/2024/03/28/apple-sues-", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/28/24115067/apple-leak-lawsuit-andrew-aude", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple sues former iOS engineer for allegedly leaking Vision Pro, Journal app details", "user": null, "vote": 0}]